DESCRIPTION OF OUR SAR Object Detection

FIRSTLY, WE USED THE DATASET FROM KAGGLE:
High resolution sar images dataset (HRSID)
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/sarribere99/high-resolution-sar-images-dataset-hrsid

MODEL 1: SFS-YOLOv8
We modified the YOLOv8n model by replacing standard convolutions in deep C2f bottleneck blocks (indices 6, 8, 12, 15, 18, 21) with SFS-Conv (Spatial-Frequency Selective Convolution), which splits channels into spatial (SPU with grouped residuals) and frequency (FPU with multi-scale/orientation FrGKConv Gabor kernels) streams, fused via CSU softmax weighting for noise-robust SAR features. Trained on the HRSID dataset (ship class, 640×640, 50 epochs), this preserved efficiency while synergizing local textures and edges. When trained from scratch for the same 50 epochs, the baseline YOLO achieved 86.9% accuracy, while the modified SFS-YOLO achieved 88.4% accuracy, showing that the proposed model improved performance in complex maritime scenes.



SECONDLY, WE USED ANOTHER DATASET FROM KAGGLE:
SARscope: Synthetic Aperture Radar Maritime Images
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kailaspsudheer/sarscope-unveiling-the-maritime-landscape

MODEL 2: Multi-Scale Residual Frequency Fusion Network++
HybridSFSNet is a baseline SFS-inspired model that combines spatial and frequency feature learning for SAR ship detection. The spatial branch uses CNN layers to extract ship shape and edge information, while the frequency branch uses FFT-based features to capture SAR texture and scattering patterns. Both features are fused using an attention mechanism and passed to a classifier, achieving a best validation accuracy of 98.75%.
To improve this, we proposed MSRFNet++ (Multi-Scale Residual Frequency Fusion Network++). It enhances the baseline by adding multi-scale spatial feature extraction using parallel 3×3 and 5×5 convolutions, residual fusion for better integration of frequency features, Batch Normalization for stable training, SE attention for suppressing SAR noise, and data augmentation for better generalization. These improvements made the model more robust and practical, achieving a best validation accuracy of 99.38%, outperforming the baseline.
